{{Infobox Christian leader | name = Hippolytus Anthony Kunnunkal OFM,Cap. | title = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Jammu–Srinagar|Bishop Emeritus of Jammu-Srinagar]] | image = | image_size = | caption = | archdiocese = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Delhi|Delhi]] | diocese = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Jammu–Srinagar|Jammu–Srinagar]] | appointed = 10 Mar 1986 | enthroned = 29 Jun 1986 | ended = 3 Apr 1998 | predecessor = Position established | successor = [[Peter Celestine Elampassery]] | ordination = 11 April 1951 | ordained_by = | consecration = 29 June 1986 | consecrated_by = [[Cardinal (Catholic Church)|Cardinal]] [[Jozef Tomko]] | birth_name = Hippolytus Anthony Kunnunkal | birth_date = 14 March 1921 | birth_place = [[Alappuzha]] [[Kerala]] India | death_date = {{death date and age|2008|8|9|1921|3|14}} | death_place = [[Kerala]] | buried = [[Kerala]] | nationality = [[India]]n | religion = [[Roman Catholic]] | residence = | parents = | spouse = | children = | occupation = | previous_post = | profession = | alma_mater = | signature = | coat_of_arms = | motto = | honorific-prefix = Most Reverend | honorific-suffix = }} Bishop Emeritus '''Dr. Hippolytus Anthony Kunnunkal, [[Order of Friars Minor Capuchin|OFM,Cap]]'''<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=dzU9NyOycG4C&pg=PA305&lpg=PA305&dq=books+by+bishop++Hippolytus+Kunnunkal&source=bl&ots=lJiLSEIlnY&sig=TmXJxEpqyeinUk_Eigl-69GAPg8&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjxrdT-wujVAhWHYo8KHcqHB5UQ6AEIQjAG#v=onepage&q=books%20by%20bishop%20%20Hippolytus%20Kunnunkal&f=false|title=Paths of Mission in India Today|last=Kanjamala|first=Augustine|date=1997|publisher=St Pauls BYB|isbn=9788171092864|language=en}}</ref>'''.'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zoominfo.com/p/Hippolytus-Kunnunkal/688666219|title=Hippolytus Kunnunkal {{!}} O.F.M. Cap. {{!}} ZoomInfo.com|website=ZoomInfo|access-date=2017-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jammusrinagardiocese.org/index.php?r=site/page&view=history|title=Diocese of Jammu Srinagar {{!}} History|website=jammusrinagardiocese.org|language=en|access-date=2017-08-21}}</ref> was first Indian [[Apostolic prefect|Prefect Apostolic]] and First [[Bishop in the Catholic Church|Bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Jammu–Srinagar|Roman Catholic Diocese of Jammu-Srinagar]].
== Early life == He was born on 14 March 1921 in [[Alappuzha|Alappuzha city]] in the state of [[Kerala]], India.
== Priesthood == He was Ordained a Priest on 11 April 1951. He was a missionary priest belonging to [[Order of Friars Minor Capuchin]].
== Prefecture == He was Appointed [[Apostolic prefect|Prefect Apostolic]] of [[Jammu and Kashmir]] on 11 November 1978.
== Episcopate == He was Consecrated Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Jammu–Srinagar]] on 29 June 1986. While bishop of Jammu Sringar, he started an initiative to translate the Bible into [[Kashmiri language|Kashmiri]], which would be completed in 2011, after his death.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Carvalho|first1=Nirmala|title=Kashmiri translation of Bible completed, the work of a convert|url=http://www.asianews.it/news-en/Kashmiri-translation-of-Bible-completed,-the-work-of-a-convert-20892.html|website=AsiaNews.it|accessdate=17 June 2017|date=28 February 2011}}</ref> He died on 9 August 2008.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org|title=Catholic-Hierarchy: Its Bishops and Dioceses, Current and Past|last=Cheney|first=David M.|website=www.catholic-hierarchy.org|access-date=2017-04-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/jamm0.htm|title=Diocese of Jammu–Srinagar, India|work=GCatholic|access-date=2017-04-24}}</ref>
